  "body": "[Equation 37](https://github.com/ethereum/yellowpaper/blob/master/Paper.tex#L451) refers that `gasLimit` should be a natural number. Why couldn't it be bound to N256?\r\n\r\nI am confused because various Ethereuem clients implement this field in different ways:\r\n- Parity: https://github.com/paritytech/parity-ethereum/blob/master/ethcore/types/src/header.rs#L79\r\n- Geth: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/types/block.go#L80",
